From Matt Landau Subject Re Asynchronous X Windows In nova Stewart Ellis writes Is there anyway to use X Windows over an async line Clearly you could use x It is X No it isn' It is the X Window System or or X or any of a number of other designations accepted by the X In fact doing man X on pretty much any machine will tell you The X Consortium requests that the following names be used when referring to this software X X Window System X Version X Window System Version There is no such thing as X Windows or X Window despite the repeated misuse of the forms by the trade This probably tells you something about how much to trust the trade rags if they can't even get the NAME of the window system right why should one trust anything else they have to say With regard to dialup implementations there are You can buy serial terminals from a couple of companies including both GraphOn and In fact I'm composing this from an NCD running over serial lines across kbaud NCD also sells a software only package that provides XRemote which is NCD's implementation of serial for PC' There may be other such software packages is supposed to include a standardized compression scheme for running over low speed It's called Low Bandwidth X LBX and is based on improved versions of the techniques used in NCD's It seems likely that once LBX is released as a Consortium standard there will be several vendors willing to supply implementations for various sorts of Followups directed to Matt Landau Waiting for a flash of enlightenment in all this blood and thunder